title: Untitled. by Courtney Love
description: One of rock's most provocative figures, Courtney Love rose to fame as singer and songwriter for rock band Hole. She would later become renowned as the widow of Nirvana frontman, Kurt Cobain. Courtney's memoir reveals her story as she lived it: from her marriage to Kurt, through to her relationships and her multiple reinventions.
author: Courtney Love
